01:07:40,199 --> 01:07:42,793
[ Champagne Cork Pops ]

922
01:07:42,869 --> 01:07:46,032
You seem tense tonight,
Mr. President.

923
01:07:46,105 --> 01:07:48,596
Oh, well, you know,
I have a lot on my mind,

924
01:07:48,674 --> 01:07:53,111
what, with preserving the Union
and my wife going crazy and all.

925
01:07:53,179 --> 01:07:56,114
[Audience Applauding]

926
01:07:57,350 --> 01:08:00,319
Can I help you find something,
Mr. President ?

927
01:08:00,386 --> 01:08:02,854
Yeah, I'm looking
for my pager.

928
01:08:02,922 --> 01:08:06,016
- Your what, sir ?
- My pager. It's this...

929
01:08:06,092 --> 01:08:08,253
little red plastic thingy.

930
01:08:08,327 --> 01:08:11,421
Looks kind of like
a cell phone, only smaller.

931
01:08:11,497 --> 01:08:14,022
- [ Groans ]
- I'm sorry ! Sorry !

932
01:08:18,004 --> 01:08:21,030
Ha ! Ha ! All right.
No problem. No problem !

933
01:08:21,107 --> 01:08:23,701
No problem ! No problem.

934
01:08:23,776 --> 01:08:26,609
Sicsemper tyrannis !

935
01:08:26,679 --> 01:08:28,772
Wait !

936
01:08:28,848 --> 01:08:30,782
Okay.

937
01:08:30,850 --> 01:08:32,351
- [Gunshot]
- [Screams]

938
01:08:32,351 --> 01:08:32,942
- [Gunshot]
- [Screams]

939
01:08:41,327 --> 01:08:43,261
[ Clears Throat ]

940
01:08:47,767 --> 01:08:52,602
- You're late, Richards.
- Uh, yes, sir. I'm very sorry.
It won't happen again.

941
01:08:52,672 --> 01:08:56,108
See that it doesn't. I don't think
a person with your extremely limited...

942
01:08:56,175 --> 01:08:59,440
personal and professional skills
can afford to push the envelope.

943
01:08:59,512 --> 01:09:01,946
Yes, sir.

944
01:09:04,350 --> 01:09:06,284
Thank you, sir.

945
01:09:14,329 --> 01:09:16,627
- Creep.
- [ Typing ]

946
01:09:16,698 --> 01:09:20,156
So, tell me, how was it ?
I'm dying to know.

947
01:09:20,235 --> 01:09:22,169
What are you doing here ?

948
01:09:22,237 --> 01:09:24,330
Just think of me
as a computer virus.

949
01:09:24,405 --> 01:09:26,873
I think of you as a plague.

950
01:09:26,941 --> 01:09:31,241
Now, will you get off
my screen ? I have work to do.

951
01:09:31,312 --> 01:09:34,110
Whoa. What's this whole
"get thee behind me" thing ?

952
01:09:34,182 --> 01:09:37,049
We still have business
here, Mr. Richards.

953
01:09:37,118 --> 01:09:39,518
No, not now.
I told you, I've got work to do.

954
01:09:39,587 --> 01:09:42,317
And besides, I've only got two wishes
left and I don't wanna screw 'em up.

955
01:09:42,390 --> 01:09:44,950
Correction.
You have one wish left.

956
01:09:47,562 --> 01:09:49,928
Nice try.
I've got two more coming.

957
01:09:49,998 --> 01:09:52,159
Nuh-uh. Count 'em, baby.

958
01:09:52,233 --> 01:09:55,930
- You were President
of the United States.
- Yeah, okay, one.

959
01:09:56,004 --> 01:09:59,963
You were a charming, handsome,
articulate, celebrated author
and raconteur.

960
01:10:00,041 --> 01:10:03,101
Uh-huh, yeah. And you turned me
into a flaming homosexual.

961
01:10:03,177 --> 01:10:05,543
- Professional basketball player.
- Three.

962
01:10:05,613 --> 01:10:07,638
The sensitive, caring,
artistic guy was four.

963
01:10:07,715 --> 01:10:10,183
And the Columbian drug lord was five.
That means I have two more coming.

964
01:10:10,251 --> 01:10:12,242
You forgot the Big Mac
and Coke.

965
01:10:12,320 --> 01:10:14,618
What ? That wasn't a wish.

966
01:10:14,689 --> 01:10:18,955
What do you call it ? You said,
"I wish" and I got it for you.
Sounds like a wish to me.

967
01:10:19,027 --> 01:10:21,393
No ! No, no, no.
No, that's not fair !

968
01:10:21,462 --> 01:10:24,158
Fair ? Who do you think
you're talking to ?

969
01:10:24,232 --> 01:10:27,258
I don't recall anybody ever
accusing me of being fair before.

970
01:10:27,335 --> 01:10:31,567
- I think I'm insulted.
- What ? No, this isn't right.
You can't do this.

971
01:10:31,639 --> 01:10:33,573
Well, what are you gonna
do about it ? Sue me ?

972
01:10:33,641 --> 01:10:38,738
No, that's it ! I've had it with you.
The whole deal is off.

973
01:10:38,813 --> 01:10:40,747
Off!

974
01:10:41,816 --> 01:10:43,807
Shut up !

975
01:10:43,885 --> 01:10:46,149
[Pipe Organ]

976
01:10:59,133 --> 01:11:01,260
Are you all right ?

977
01:11:01,336 --> 01:11:03,804
Uh, not really.

978
01:11:03,871 --> 01:11:05,668
Uh--

979
01:11:05,740 --> 01:11:08,402
I need to talk to God.

980
01:11:08,476 --> 01:11:12,936
That's the power of prayer. Just say
what's in your heart and He hears.

981
01:11:13,014 --> 01:11:18,145
No, you don't understand.
I really need to talk to Him now.

982
01:11:18,219 --> 01:11:22,246
- It's urgent.
- Is it something you could tell me ?

983
01:11:22,323 --> 01:11:25,815
Um, no, it's personal.

984
01:11:25,893 --> 01:11:28,760
There's nothing you could say
that I wouldn't understand.

985
01:11:28,830 --> 01:11:30,991
Um--

986
01:11:31,065 --> 01:11:33,295
Why don't you just try me ?

987
01:11:33,368 --> 01:11:37,031
Okay, a few days ago I sold my soul
to the Devil for seven wishes.

988
01:11:37,105 --> 01:11:39,573
I've already had five of them,
but the Devil says I've had six,

989
01:11:39,641 --> 01:11:43,702
but I'm not counting
the Big Mac and Coke and she is
and I don't think that's fair.

990
01:11:43,778 --> 01:11:45,643
Do you ?

991
01:11:48,516 --> 01:11:50,984
- This is so unnecessary.
- You're coming downtown with us.

992
01:11:51,052 --> 01:11:55,284
- I'm telling you, the Devil
gypped me for a ham burger !
- Tell your story to the sergeant.

993
01:11:55,356 --> 01:11:57,824
So, do you have
a copy of this contract ?

994
01:11:57,892 --> 01:12:00,326
No. I told you,
she keeps it in her office.

995
01:12:00,395 --> 01:12:03,262
- At this nightclub in Oakland ?
- Yes, at a nightclub,

996
01:12:03,331 --> 01:12:05,390
and no I can't tell you
where it is.

997
01:12:05,466 --> 01:12:07,491
Because you promised
the Devil you wouldn't ?

998
01:12:07,568 --> 01:12:09,593
No, because she drove,
that's why !

999
01:12:09,671 --> 01:12:12,834
Right, in a Lamborghini Diablo.

1000
01:12:12,907 --> 01:12:15,603
- Look, Officer--
- Sergeant.

1001
01:12:15,677 --> 01:12:19,670
Sergeant, I know my rights. I don't
have to talk to you without a lawyer.

1002
01:12:19,747 --> 01:12:22,147
So, you either book me
or you let me go.

1003
01:12:22,216 --> 01:12:26,482
Gee, are those my choices ?
Oh, what do I do, what do I do ?

1004
01:12:26,554 --> 01:12:29,614
I choose "book you."
Throw him in the lockup.

1005
01:12:29,691 --> 01:12:33,218
- Arraignment in the morning.
Drunk and disorderly.
- What ? Hey !

1006
01:12:33,294 --> 01:12:36,092
- Recommending psychiatric evaluation.
- It's her ! She's the Devil !

1007
01:12:36,164 --> 01:12:39,725
One more word out of you and I'll pop
you one, you goddamn wacko bastard.

1008
01:12:39,801 --> 01:12:42,599
Now, move it.

1009
01:12:48,609 --> 01:12:51,134
Spread 'em.

1010
01:12:51,212 --> 01:12:53,806
There's no point
fighting about this.

1011
01:12:53,881 --> 01:12:57,783
You have to learn
to accept the inevitable.

1012
01:12:57,852 --> 01:13:02,380
We're all doomed anyway, so you might
as well just get with the program,

1013
01:13:02,457 --> 01:13:05,324
wish your way out of here
and move on.

1014
01:13:08,162 --> 01:13:12,963
I wasn't kidding when I said
I liked you. I do, Elliot.

1015
01:13:13,034 --> 01:13:16,128
I think you have
massive potential.

1016
01:13:16,204 --> 01:13:19,503
If you're looking
at an eternity in Hell,

1017
01:13:19,574 --> 01:13:24,102
let me tell you, it wouldn't hurt
to have a friend like me.

1018
01:13:31,919 --> 01:13:35,787
So you just think about that
and give me a call when you're ready.

1019
01:13:38,893 --> 01:13:40,827
[ Cell Door Shuts ]

1020
01:13:43,731 --> 01:13:45,926
[Man]
She's the devil, that one.

1021
01:13:46,000 --> 01:13:47,934
What ?

1022
01:13:54,375 --> 01:13:56,309
I said, she's the devil,
that lady cop.

1023
01:13:56,377 --> 01:13:58,311
Oh.

1024
01:14:00,248 --> 01:14:02,580
Yeah, I guess.

1025
01:14:02,650 --> 01:14:06,848
- So, what you in for, brother ?
- Eternity.

1026
01:14:06,921 --> 01:14:10,652
Ooh. That's a long time.

1027
01:14:10,725 --> 01:14:12,920
You must've did
some really bad shit.

1028
01:14:12,994 --> 01:14:14,928
Yeah.

1029
01:14:15,997 --> 01:14:18,124
I sold my soul.

1030
01:14:18,199 --> 01:14:20,360
Hope you got something
good for it.

1031
01:14:20,434 --> 01:14:22,800
As a matter of fact,
I got nothing for it.

1032
01:14:22,870 --> 01:14:25,600
That's a really bad deal,
if you ask me.

1033
01:14:27,608 --> 01:14:30,008
I'm not asking you.

1034
01:14:34,448 --> 01:14:37,144
Doesn't really matter, though.

1035
01:14:37,218 --> 01:14:40,449
- You can't sell your soul, anyway.
- Oh, really ?

1036
01:14:40,521 --> 01:14:42,785
Why do you say that ?

1037
01:14:42,857 --> 01:14:47,191
Doesn't really belong to you
in the first place. No way, no how.

1038
01:14:48,462 --> 01:14:50,726
So, who does it belong to ?

1039
01:14:54,902 --> 01:14:57,268
It belongs to God,

1040
01:14:57,338 --> 01:15:01,638
that universal spirit that animates
and binds all things in existence.

1041
01:15:04,045 --> 01:15:05,979
The Devil gonna
try to confuse you.

1042
01:15:06,047 --> 01:15:07,981
But that's her gig.

1043
01:15:08,049 --> 01:15:13,214
But in the end, you're gonna see
clear to who and what you are
and what you're here to do.

1044
01:15:13,287 --> 01:15:16,620
Now, you're gonna make some mistakes
along the way. Everybody does.

1045
01:15:16,691 --> 01:15:19,251
But if you just open up
your heart. ..

1046
01:15:19,327 --> 01:15:21,887
and open up your mind,

1047
01:15:21,963 --> 01:15:23,931
you'll get it.

1048
01:15:25,166 --> 01:15:27,327
Who are you ?

1049
01:15:30,504 --> 01:15:32,563
Just a friend, brother.

1050
01:15:32,640 --> 01:15:35,108
Just a really good friend.

1051
01:16:27,061 --> 01:16:28,995
[ Techno Dance ]

1052
01:16:40,574 --> 01:16:42,599
[ Chattering ]

1053
01:16:47,495 --> 01:16:51,431
[Crowd Shouting]
Elliot ! Elliot !

1054
01:16:51,499 --> 01:16:53,729
[ Man ]
You the man, Elliot !

1055
01:16:53,802 --> 01:16:58,501
Elliot, darling.
So nice of you to drop by.

1056
01:16:58,573 --> 01:17:00,905
- Come into my office.
- [ Muttering ]

1057
01:17:00,976 --> 01:17:04,571
Oh, don't worry about them, darling.
They're having a fabulous time.

1058
01:17:04,646 --> 01:17:07,240
Pathetic, aren't they ?

1059
01:17:07,315 --> 01:17:12,912
Everybody wants to go to the party,
but nobody wants to pay the piper.

1060
01:17:12,988 --> 01:17:17,891
- Are you--
- Don't get too excited.
It's just a Halloween costume.

1061
01:17:17,959 --> 01:17:20,894
Anyway, Elliot, my darling,
have you thought of your last wish ?

1062
01:17:20,962 --> 01:17:25,296
- No.
- I hate to put a rush on this,
but there is a time limit.

1063
01:17:25,367 --> 01:17:27,562
Read your contract.

1064
01:17:36,177 --> 01:17:38,577
I really don't want another wish.

1065
01:17:38,647 --> 01:17:42,242
[ Scoffs ] That's funny.
Do you think this halo's too much ?

1066
01:17:42,317 --> 01:17:45,946
No. I really don't want it.

1067
01:17:48,290 --> 01:17:52,420
What do you mean, you don't want it ?
You get seven wishes.

1068
01:17:52,494 --> 01:17:54,462
There's nothing I want.

1069
01:17:55,764 --> 01:17:57,698
Well, there are things
that I want,

1070
01:17:57,766 --> 01:17:59,791
but nothing
that you can give me.

1071
01:17:59,868 --> 01:18:02,996
What is that supposed to mean ?

1072
01:18:03,071 --> 01:18:05,335
Well, um,

1073
01:18:05,407 --> 01:18:09,070
last night when I was lying in jail,
I was talking to this guy,

1074
01:18:09,144 --> 01:18:11,977
I realized that wishing
just doesn't work.

1075
01:18:12,047 --> 01:18:13,981
All my life I wished
to be better looking,

1076
01:18:14,049 --> 01:18:16,984
to be richer, to be successful,
talented, whatever.

1077
01:18:17,052 --> 01:18:19,953
And I always thought,
"Wouldn't it be great if someone
could just wave a magic wand...

1078
01:18:20,021 --> 01:18:21,955
and make that happen.,,

1079
01:18:22,023 --> 01:18:24,821
Well, I realized that
it doesn't work by magic.

1080
01:18:24,893 --> 01:18:27,657
I think I'm gonna be sick.

1081
01:18:29,030 --> 01:18:31,555
I've been starting
to think that...

1082
01:18:31,633 --> 01:18:35,160
it really isn't that important
how far we go in life anyway.

1083
01:18:35,236 --> 01:18:37,295
It's how we get there
that really matters.

1084
01:18:37,372 --> 01:18:39,306
Oh.

1085
01:18:39,374 --> 01:18:42,775
Do you know,
that is so inspiring.

1086
01:18:44,179 --> 01:18:46,170
So, it's okay ?

1087
01:18:46,247 --> 01:18:49,080
Well, no, Elliot.
I'm afraid it's not okay.

1088
01:18:49,150 --> 01:18:53,314
A deal's a deal. You get
one more wish and I get your soul.

1089
01:18:53,388 --> 01:18:56,323
So, let's just get on
with it, shall we ?

1090
01:18:56,391 --> 01:18:58,882
- I'm not gonna do it.
- Oh, really ?

1091
01:18:58,960 --> 01:19:01,588
Well, before you get all hinky,
I think I should warn you,

1092
01:19:01,663 --> 01:19:03,995
I'm not all peaches
and cream, you know.

1093
01:19:04,065 --> 01:19:07,831
I do have a darker side,
and believe me, it's not pretty.

1094
01:19:07,902 --> 01:19:10,700
Now, you can go easy
or you can go hard,

1095
01:19:10,772 --> 01:19:13,866
but one way or another
I will get your soul !

1096
01:19:13,942 --> 01:19:16,035
I'm not gonna do it.

1097
01:19:16,111 --> 01:19:19,308
There's nothing that you can
say or do that will make me.

1098
01:19:19,381 --> 01:19:21,315
Oh, I think you'll
change your mind.

1099
01:19:21,383 --> 01:19:25,114
I'm just gonna slip into something
a little more terrifying.
See you in Hell !

1100
01:19:26,388 --> 01:19:29,448
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Roaring ]

1101
01:19:32,827 --> 01:19:35,125
- [ Roaring ]
- Wait, wait, wait.

1102
01:19:35,196 --> 01:19:38,256
Wait a minute ! Wait !
[Screams]

1103
01:19:38,333 --> 01:19:41,530
Wait !
[ Screaming ]

1104
01:19:41,603 --> 01:19:44,834
Now listen to me,
you disgusting little maggot !

1105
01:19:44,906 --> 01:19:49,366
This is your last chance
before the big weenie roast.

1106
01:19:49,444 --> 01:19:52,641
Make a wish or
forever burn in Hell !

1107
01:19:52,714 --> 01:19:54,875
Okay ! Okay !

1108
01:19:54,949 --> 01:19:57,509
I wish--

1109
01:19:57,585 --> 01:20:00,315
I wish that Alison
has a happy life.

1110
01:20:00,388 --> 01:20:02,652
Oh, God.

1111
01:20:02,724 --> 01:20:04,988
[ Screaming ]

1112
01:20:27,949 --> 01:20:31,817
- Is this Heaven ?
- Heaven ? God, no, it's the courthouse.

1113
01:20:31,886 --> 01:20:37,017
I'm just meeting a couple of lawyers
for lunch-- clients of mine. Come on.

1114
01:20:37,091 --> 01:20:39,355
Well, wait.

1115
01:20:39,427 --> 01:20:41,520
What happened to the whole...

1116
01:20:41,596 --> 01:20:45,555
you know, fire and
the big horny guy with the--

1117
01:20:45,633 --> 01:20:48,067
Oh, just a few special effects.

1118
01:20:48,136 --> 01:20:50,764
Sort of the Universal Studios
Tour of Evil.

1119
01:20:50,839 --> 01:20:54,605
Normally it works pretty well,
but evidently you weren't going for it.

1120
01:20:54,676 --> 01:20:57,338
- That last wish of yours
was a deal breaker.
- What ?

1121
01:20:57,412 --> 01:20:59,710
Nobody ever reads the contract.

1122
01:20:59,781 --> 01:21:04,718
Article 147, paragraph 9, subsection 3:
"Selfless Acts of Redemption."

1123
01:21:04,786 --> 01:21:07,414
- Huh ?
- Basically, it says...

1124
01:21:07,489 --> 01:21:10,515
if you commit one truly benevolent act,
it voids the contract.

1125
01:21:10,592 --> 01:21:15,154
- So I get to keep my soul ?
- Yes, you get to keep your soul.

1126
01:21:16,998 --> 01:21:20,365
Yes ! Oh, yes !

1127
01:21:20,435 --> 01:21:23,734
Yes, I get to keep my soul !

1128
01:21:23,805 --> 01:21:26,467
Whoo ! Hoo !

1129
01:21:26,541 --> 01:21:29,806
Hoo !

1130
01:21:29,878 --> 01:21:32,779
On November 16, I'll have
been doing this for 6,000 years...

1131
01:21:32,847 --> 01:21:35,873
and you're the first person
to give away one of their wishes.

1132
01:21:35,950 --> 01:21:38,942
I hope it's not the beginning
of a trend. You're not gonna
tell anyone, are you ?

1133
01:21:39,020 --> 01:21:41,352
No, no, I promise. Nope.

1134
01:21:42,857 --> 01:21:47,351
I don't get it, though.
I mean, why are you... being nice ?

1135
01:21:47,428 --> 01:21:50,693
Look, Elliot, I'm gonna
let you in on a little secret.

1136
01:21:50,765 --> 01:21:54,895
The whole good and evil thing,
you know, Him and me,

1137
01:21:54,969 --> 01:21:57,199
it really comes down to you.

1138
01:21:57,272 --> 01:21:59,706
You don't have to look
very hard for Heaven and Hell.

1139
01:21:59,774 --> 01:22:02,242
They're right here on Earth.

1140
01:22:02,310 --> 01:22:04,244
You make the choice.

1141
01:22:04,312 --> 01:22:06,371
And I guess
you just made yours.

1142
01:22:06,447 --> 01:22:08,540
So, I can go now ?

1143
01:22:08,616 --> 01:22:10,880
Unless you want
another seven wishes.

1144
01:22:10,952 --> 01:22:12,886
[ Chuckles ]
No thanks.

1145
01:22:12,954 --> 01:22:15,047
I didn't think so.

1146
01:22:16,257 --> 01:22:18,191
I really liked you, you know.

1147
01:22:20,094 --> 01:22:22,654
Well, to tell you the truth,

1148
01:22:22,730 --> 01:22:25,198
you've been the best friend
I've ever had.

1149
01:22:25,266 --> 01:22:28,429
Oh, dear.
Don't go gushy on me now.

1150
01:22:30,138 --> 01:22:33,505
Go on. Go.
You'll scare the fish away.

1151
01:22:53,728 --> 01:22:56,492
Alison. Hi.

